<HL>
   Business Brief -- Hanson PLC:
   Marvin Electric and Others
   Sold for Over $62 Million
</HL>
<DATE>
05/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   HAN
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Hanson Industries, the U.S. arm of Hanson PLC, the British
industrial company, said it sold a group of companies
including, Los Angeles-based Marvin Electric Mfg. Co., for
more than $62 million.
   Marvin, a maker of incandescent and high intensity
discharge lighting, had operating profit of $392,000 and
sales of $13.9 million in the six months ended March 31.
Marvin, acquired in 1987 as part of the Kidde Inc.
acquisition, was sold for $18.5 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Hanson said it also sold a number of other businesses for
more than $31.8 million in cash and $11.7 million in notes;
the businesses in the past fiscal year had sales of $90.5
million and pretax losses of $86,000.
</TEXT>
